The paper discusses the development of tools and methodologies to improve spreadsheet quality, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also focuses on the analysis of formula structures and data dependencies, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and database systems (cs.DB). The study also involves the visualization of large spreadsheets, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the analysis of errors in a real-world industrial context, which falls under the cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category.
